from email.mime.text import MIMEText

def send_email(sender, recipient, subject, message):
    """Sends an email using the provided sender and recipient email addresses, subject and message text."""
    server = smtplib.SMTP("smtp.gmail.com", 587) # Gmail SMTP server
    server.starttls() # Enable SSL/TLS encryption
    server.login(sender, "password") # Authenticate with Gmail
    message = MIMEText(message, "plain") # Create an email message object with the provided text
    message["From"] = sender # Set the From header of the email to the sender's email address
    message["To"] = recipient # Set the To header of the email to the recipient's email address
    message["Subject"] = subject # Set the Subject header of the email to the provided subject text
